Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 07/2020]
Title: SEAT: FRONT SEAT ASSEMBLY (for Manual Seat): DISASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2020 MY Prius [11/2015 - 07/2020]

DISASSEMBLY

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

CAUTION:

Wear protective gloves. Sharp areas on the parts may injure your hands.

HINT:

  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.
  • The following procedure is for the LH side.

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE OCCUPANT DETECTION ECU (for Front Passenger Side)

Click here

2. REMOVE FRONT SEAT INNER BELT ASSEMBLY (for Driver Side)

Click here

3. REMOVE FRONT SEAT INNER BELT ASSEMBLY (for Front Passenger Side)

Click here

4. DISCONNECT SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEATBACK COVER

(a) Disconnect the rubber band of the separate type front seatback cover.

5. REMOVE VERTICAL ADJUSTING HANDLE (for Driver Side)

(a) Operate the vertical adjusting handle and using a screwdriver with its tip wrapped with protective tape, disengage the claw and remove the vertical adjusting handle as shown in the illustration.

*a

Protective Tape

Remove in this direction

6. REMOVE NO. 1 RECLINING HINGE COVER

(a) Using a screwdriver with its tip wrapped with protective tape, disengage the claw.

*a

Protective Tape

(b) Disengage the guide to remove the No. 1 reclining hinge cover.

7. REMOVE RECLINING ADJUSTER RELEASE HANDLE

(a) Remove the reclining adjuster release handle.

8. REMOVE SEAT ADJUSTER COVER CAP (for Driver Side)

(a) Using a screwdriver with its tip wrapped with protective tape, disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Protective Tape

Remove in this direction (1)

Remove in this direction (2)

(b) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the seat adjuster cover cap as shown in the illustration.

9. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION SHIELD LH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the 2 claws.

(b) Disengage the claw and 2 guides.

(c) Using a screwdriver with its tip wrapped with protective tape, disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Protective Tape

Remove in this direction

(d) Disengage the guide to remove the front seat cushion shield LH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this direction

10. REMOVE FRONT SEAT INNER CUSHION SHIELD LH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the 2 claws.

(b) Disengage the 2 claws and 2 guides to remove the front seat inner cushion shield LH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this direction

11. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION SHIELD RH (for Front Passenger Side)

(a) Disengage the 2 claws.

(b) Disengage the claw and 2 guides.

(c) Using a screwdriver with its tip wrapped with protective tape, disengage the claw as shown in the illustration.

*a

Protective Tape

Remove in this direction

(d) Disengage the guide to remove the front seat cushion shield RH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this direction

12. REMOVE FRONT SEAT INNER CUSHION SHIELD RH (for Front Passenger Side)

(a) Disengage the 3 claws.

(b) Disengage the 2 claws and 2 guides to remove the front seat inner cushion shield RH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this direction

13. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEATBACK ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 2 hooks.

(b) w/ Seat Heater System:

(1) Disconnect the connector.

(2) Disengage the clamp.

(c) Disengage the claw and 4 clamps to separate the front seat airbag assembly wire harness.

HINT:

Disengage the 4 clamps first.

(d) Remove the 4 bolts.

(e) Disengage the 4 guides to remove the separate type front seatback assembly from the separate type front seat cushion assembly.

14. REMOVE FRONT SEAT HEADREST SUPPORT

(a) Disengage the 3 hooks.

(b) w/ Seat Heater System:

(1) Disengage the clamp.

(c) Open the 2 fasteners.

(d) Disengage the 4 claws and remove the 2 front seat headrest supports.

15. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEATBACK COVER WITH PAD

(a) Remove the separate type front seatback cover with pad.

16. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEATBACK COVER

(a) Using a screwdriver, disengage the 18 claws and remove the separate type front seatback cover from the separate type front seatback pad as shown in the illustration.

*a

Screwdriver

-

-

17. REMOVE FRONT SEATBACK HEATER ASSEMBLY (w/ Seat Heater System)

Click here

18. REMOVE FRONT SEAT AIRBAG ASSEMBLY

Click here

19. REMOVE FRONT SEATBACK SPRING SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the 2 front seatback edge protectors from the front seatback frame sub-assembly.

(b) Remove the front seatback spring sub-assembly from the front seatback frame sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this direction

20. REMOVE FRONT SEATBACK EDGE PROTECTOR

(a) Remove the 2 front seatback edge protectors from the front seatback spring sub-assembly.

21. REMOVE FRONT SEATBACK HOOK

(a) Remove the 2 front seatback hooks from the front seatback frame sub-assembly.

22. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEAT CUSHION COVER WITH PAD

(a) w/ Seat Heater System:

(1) Disengage the claw and 4 clamps to separate the front seat cushion heater assembly wire harness.

HINT:

Disengage the 4 clamps first.

(b) Disengage the 2 hooks.

(c) Disengage the 10 hooks and remove the separate type front seat cushion cover with pad.

23. REMOVE SEPARATE TYPE FRONT SEAT CUSHION COVER

(a) Using a screwdriver, disengage the 13 claws and remove the separate type front seat cushion cover from the separate type front seat cushion pad as shown in the illustration.

*a

Screwdriver

-

-

24. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION HEATER ASSEMBLY (w/ Seat Heater System)

Click here

25. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION AIRBAG ASSEMBLY RH (for Front Passenger Side)

Click here

26. REMOVE LH SEAT RECLINING ADJUSTER INSIDE COVER LH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the 4 claws to remove the LH seat reclining adjuster inside cover LH.

27. REMOVE LH SEAT RECLINING ADJUSTER INSIDE COVER RH (for Driver Side)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

28. REMOVE RH SEAT RECLINING ADJUSTER INSIDE COVER LH (for Front Passenger Side)

(a) Disengage the clamp.

(b) Disengage the 4 claws to remove the RH seat reclining adjuster inside cover LH.

29. REMOVE RH SEAT RECLINING ADJUSTER INSIDE COVER RH (for Front Passenger Side)

(a) Disengage the 4 claws to remove the RH seat reclining adjuster inside cover RH.

30. REMOVE FRONT SEAT LOWER CUSHION SHIELD LH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the hook.

*a

Hook

*b

Guide

(b) Disengage the claw and guide to remove the front seat lower cushion shield LH.

31. REMOVE FRONT SEAT LOWER CUSHION SHIELD RH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the hook.

*a

Hook

*b

Guide

(b) Disengage the claw and guide to remove the front seat lower cushion shield RH.

32. REMOVE FRONT SEAT WIRE RH (for Front Passenger Side)

(a) Disconnect each connector and disengage each clamp to remove the front seat wire RH.

33. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION WIRE HARNESS HOLDER

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the claw to remove the front seat cushion wire harness holder.

34. REMOVE FRONT SEAT CUSHION SPRING SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 6 hooks to remove the front seat cushion spring sub-assembly from the front seat adjuster assembly.

35. REMOVE SEAT TRACK ADJUSTING HANDLE

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the seat track adjusting handle from the front seat adjuster assembly.

36. REMOVE FRONT SEAT VERTICAL ADJUSTER ASSEMBLY (for Driver Side)

(a) Remove the front seat vertical adjuster assembly.

(1) Remove the 3 nuts and vertical adjuster plate.

(2) Remove the vertical adjuster spacer.

(3) Remove the front vertical adjuster brake sub-assembly LH.

37. REMOVE VERTICAL ADJUSTER BRACKET COVER LH (for Driver Side)

(a) Disengage the claw to remove the vertical adjuster bracket cover LH from the front vertical adjuster brake sub-assembly LH.
